							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lenavalencia/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ValenciaLena_CreditRyanSpencer_LoRes_NEW-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Lena Valencia" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lenavalencia/">Lena Valencia</a></h6>
										Lena Valencia’s fiction has appeared in <em>Ninth Letter</em>, <em>Epiphany</em>, <em>Joyland</em>, the anthology <em>Tiny Nightmares</em>, and elsewhere. She is the recipient of a 2019 Elizabeth George Foundation grant and holds an MFA in fiction from The New School. Originally from Los Angeles, she lives in Brooklyn, New York, where she is the managing editor and director of educational programming at One Story and the co-host of the reading series Ditmas Lit. She is the author of <em>Mystery Lights</em>.																			</div>
